Encrypt the generated token. It contains too much free authority (the
name of the underlying resource).

Figure out what to do about routing keys -- is the topic supplied in a
POST the topic of the message as sent, or a repetition of the pattern
which the subscriber subscribed with?

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

A = auth
X = public

ISubscribable:

  A subscribe(callback, topic, verify[, verify_token])
    --> 202 | 204 | 4xx | 5xx

  A unsubscribe(callback, topic, verify[, verify_token])
    --> 202 | 204 | 4xx | 5xx

IEndpoint:
  A publish(msg) --> 202 | 204 | 4xx | 5xx
  A gettoken() --> 200 | 4xx | 5xx
  X subscribe(token) --> 2xx | 404 | 4xx | 5xx
  X unsubscribe(token) --> 2xx | 404 | 4xx | 5xx
